e, England":"Newbold Verdon, Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Barri, Glamorgan, Wales":"Barri, Glamorgan, Wales","Barry, Glamorgan, Wales":"Barry, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Frankrijk","Faumont Castle, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1346–1437":"1346–1437","1338–1428":"1338–1428","1360–1424":"1360–1424","1319–1374":"1319–1374","1324–1443":"1324–1443","13 May 1428":"13 May 1428","23 December 1424":"23 December 1424","1374":"1374","1360":"1360","1437":"1437","1338":"1338","August 1374":"August 1374","1424":"1424","1346":"1346","1324":"1324","1345":"1345","1443":"1443","1319":"1319","1428":"1428","Gwlad Morgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Newbold Verdon, Leicestershire, England":"Newbold Verdon, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Barri, Glamorgan, Wales":"Barri, Glamorgan, Wales","Barry, Glamorgan, Wales":"Barry, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","Faumont Castle, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Saint-John","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of English and American (of French origin)   St. John  ."],"variants":[{"name":"St. John","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in France called Saint-Jean (see   St. Jean  ).","Americanized form of French <b>Saint-Jean</b> (see   St. Jean  ). Compare   Saintjohn  ."]}]},{"name":"Oliver","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a French name, <i>Olivier</i>, recorded as the name of one of Charlemagne's paladins (retainers), the close companion in arms of Roland in the Chanson de Roland. Whereas Roland is headstrong and rash, Oliver is thoughtful and cautious. Ostensibly this name derives from Late Latin <i>olivarius</i> ‘olive tree’ (  compare  Olive  ), but Charlemagne's other paladins all bear solidly Germanic names, so it is more probably an altered form of a Germanic name, perhaps distantly connected with Old Norse <i>Óleifr</i> ‘ancestral relic’. It has remained in more or less continuous use since the medieval period, becoming ever more popular since the 1980s."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Oliver de Saint-John was born in 1346, in Barry, Glamorgan, Wales, his father, Sir John St John, was 27 and his mother, Isabel De Paveley, was 22. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth de la Bere. He died in 1437, in Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France, at the age of 91."},"et":{"1346–1437":"1346–1437","1338–1428":"1338–1428","1360–1424":"1360–1424","1319–1374":"1319–1374","1324–1443":"1324–1443","13 May 1428":"13. mai 1428","23 December 1424":"23. detsember 1424","1374":"1374","1360":"1360","1437":"1437","1338":"1338","August 1374":"august 1374","1424":"1424","1346":"1346","1324":"1324","1345":"1345","1443":"1443","1319":"1319","1428":"1428","Gwlad Morgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Newbold Verdon, Leicestershire, England":"Newbold Verdon, Leicestershire, I